context: The school newspaper of the University of Kansas is <a0_0><b5_0>University Daily Kansan<b5_0/><a0_0/>, which placed first in the <a1_0><b6_0>Intercollegiate Writing Competition<b6_0/><a1_0/> of the prestigious William Randolph Hearst Writing Foundation competition, often called "The Pulitzers of College Journalism" in <a2_0><b7_0>2007<b7_0/><a2_0/>. In Winter 2008, a group of students created <a3_0><b8_0>KUpedia<b8_0/><a3_0/>, a wiki about all things KU. They have received student funding for operations in 2008–09. The KU Department of English publishes the Coal City Review, an annual literary journal of prose, poetry, reviews and illustrations. The Review typically features the work of many writers, but periodically spotlights one author, as in the case of 2006 Nelson Poetry Book Award-winner Voyeur Poems by <a4_0><b9_0>Matthew Porubsky<b9_0/><a4_0/>.
